Shipping Management Module
The Shipping Management Module manages the shipping process for customer orders, including shipping cost calculation, shipment tracking, and integration with logistics providers. It ensures products are shipped efficiently and customers can monitor their delivery status at every stage.

üìã Features
1. Shipping Cost Calculation
Calculates shipping costs based on package weight, delivery location, and shipping method.

2. Shipping Dashboard (Admin)
Allows admins to view all orders with shipping details:

Courier service

Tracking number

Shipping status

Shipping cost

3. Track Shipment (Customer)
Customers can track their shipment status via a tracking number.

4. Update Shipping Information (Admin)
Admins can update shipping details such as tracking numbers and courier info after order dispatch.

üóÑÔ∏è Database Design
Table Name: shipping

Column Name	Data Type	Description
shipping_id	INT, PK, AUTO_INCREMENT	Unique identifier for each shipping entry
order_id	INT, FK	References orders(order_id)
courier_service	VARCHAR(100)	Courier/shipping provider
tracking_number	VARCHAR(100)	Unique tracking number
shipping_status	VARCHAR(50)	Shipment status (Shipped, In Transit, Delivered)
shipping_cost	DECIMAL(10,2)	Shipping cost for the order
created_at	DATETIME	Shipping initiated timestamp
updated_at	DATETIME	Last updated timestamp
SQL Script:

sql
CREATE TABLE shipping (
  shipping_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  order_id INT,
  courier_service VARCHAR(100),
  tracking_number VARCHAR(100),
  shipping_status VARCHAR(50),
  shipping_cost DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
  created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  updated_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id)
);
